private

Applies an in-place mod to the given attribute.

This correctly update the attribute's aggregator, updates the attribute set property, and invokes the OnDirty callbacks. This does not invoke Pre/PostGameplayEffectExecute calls on the attribute set. This does no tag checking, application requirements, immunity, etc. No GameplayEffectSpec is created or is applied! This should only be used in cases where applying a real GameplayEffectSpec is too slow or not possible.

◆ GetActivatableGameplayAbilitySpecsByAllMatchingTags()

GAMEPLAYABILITIES_API void UAbilitySystemComponent::GetActivatableGameplayAbilitySpecsByAllMatchingTags ( const FGameplayTagContainer & GameplayTagContainer,
TArray< struct FGameplayAbilitySpec * > & MatchingGameplayAbilities,
bool bOnlyAbilitiesThatSatisfyTagRequirements = true ) const
private

Gets all Activatable Gameplay Abilities that match all tags in GameplayTagContainer AND for which DoesAbilitySatisfyTagRequirements() is true.

The latter requirement allows this function to find the correct ability without requiring advanced knowledge. For example, if there are two "Melee" abilities, one of which requires a weapon and one of which requires being unarmed, then those abilities can use Blocking and Required tags to determine when they can fire. Using the Satisfying Tags requirements simplifies a lot of usage cases. For example, Behavior Trees can use various decorators to test an ability fetched using this mechanism as well as the Task to execute the ability without needing to know that there even is more than one such ability.

◆ ReadyForReplication()

virtual GAMEPLAYABILITIES_API void UAbilitySystemComponent::ReadyForReplication ( )
overridevirtual

ReadyForReplication gets called on replicated components when their owning actor is officially ready for replication.

Called after InitializeComponent but before BeginPlay. From there it will only be set false when the component is destroyed. This is where you want to register your replicated subobjects if you already possess some. A component can get replicated before HasBegunPlay() is true if inside a tick or in BeginPlay() an RPC is called on it. Requires component to be registered, initialized and set to replicate.

Reimplemented from UGameplayTasksComponent.
